-- Turkish Stocks: Adana Cimento, Frigo-Pak, Karsan Are Active
-- B y   B e n j a m i n   H a r v e y
-- 2012-07-20T16:09:17Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-07-20/turkish-stocks-adana-cimento-boyner-buyuk-move-in-istanbul.html
Turkey â€™s benchmark  ISE National 100
Index (XU100)  fell 0.9 percent to 61,792.16 at the close in Istanbul,
falling for a fourth day and extending its loss this week to 1.4
percent.  The following shares were active. Stock symbols are in
parentheses.  Adana Cimento Sanayii TAS (ADANA)  , a cement maker based
in Adana in southern Turkey, declined 1.5 percent to 0.68 liras
after Sabah newspaper reported that Sonmez Holding AS will build
a $165 million cement plant in the same province.  Frigo-Pak Gida Maddeleri Sanayi & Ticaret AS (FRIGO)  , an
Istanbul-based processor and packager of food products, jumped
5.3 percent to 1 lira after saying it signed an accord for
Universe Capital Partners LLC to invest in the company.  Karsan Otomotiv Sanayii & Ticaret AS (KARSN)  , a Turkish
motor vehicle maker, rose the most in almost a month, adding 2.6
percent to 1.19 liras after saying it won an Istanbul
municipality auction to supply 200 natural gas-fired buses and
spare parts.  To contact the reporter on this story:
